"title": "7212: exile",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7212: exile",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A period of absence from one's homeland, often imposed as a form of punishment. The OT regards Israel's exile in Babylon as a form of divine punishment for past sin and as an opportunity for renewal and rededication.</p>\n<h2>Exile commanded by God for his purposes</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:1\">GEN 12:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:4\">GEN 11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:8-Gen11:9\">GEN 11:8–11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:11\">PSA 44:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:6\">ZEC 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:13-Matt2:15\">MAT 2:13–2:15</a></p>\n<h2>Exile imposed as a form of punishment</h2>\n<h3>On individuals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:23\">GEN 3:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:14\">GEN 17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:20\">LEV 7:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:29\">LEV 18:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:8\">LEV 19:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:17\">LEV 20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:36\">DEU 28:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:25\">1SA 12:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:15-2Kgs24:16\">2KI 24:15–24:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:4\">2CH 36:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:10\">2CH 36:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech5:3\">ZEC 5:3</a></p>\n<h3>On Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:33\">LEV 26:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:25-Deut4:27\">DEU 4:25–4:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:36\">DEU 28:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:64\">DEU 28:64</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:46\">1KI 8:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:9-2Kgs18:12\">2KI 18:9–18:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:11\">2KI 25:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:26\">1CH 5:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:20\">2CH 36:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:13\">ISA 5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:8-Jer25:11\">JER 25:8–25:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:10\">JER 27:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:27\">AMO 5:27</a></p>\n<h3>On other nations</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:5\">AMO 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:15\">AMO 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:5\">AMO 5:5</a></p>\n<h2>Exile through military defeat</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:9-2Kgs18:11\">2KI 18:9–18:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:29\">2KI 15:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:16\">2KI 24:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr8:6\">1CH 8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:8\">JOB 30:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:17\">JER 50:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:1-Joel3:2\">JOL 3:1–3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic1:16\">MIC 1:16</a></p>\n<h2>Exile through personal choice</h2>\n<h3>To escape danger</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:15\">EXO 2:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:6-Gen16:8\">GEN 16:6–16:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:6-Gen35:7\">GEN 35:6–35:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:18\">1SA 19:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:10\">1SA 21:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:38-2Sam13:39\">2SA 13:38–13:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:9\">REV 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>To escape natural disaster</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:5-Gen46:6\">GEN 46:5–46:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:1-Gen26:3\">GEN 26:1–26:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:1\">RUT 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>To support friends</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:19-2Sam15:21\">2SA 15:19–15:21</a></p>\n<h3>At the advice of others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:42-Gen27:45\">GEN 27:42–27:45</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:12-1Sam20:13\">1SA 20:12–20:13</a></p>\n<h2>Those exiled because of their faith</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:1\">1PE 1:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:1\">ACT 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:19\">ACT 11:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8-Heb11:9\">HEB 11:8–11:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:14-Heb11:15\">HEB 11:14–11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:27\">HEB 11:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:38\">HEB 11:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:1\">JAS 1:1</a></p>\n<h2>God does not intend exile to be permanent</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:14\">2SA 14:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:4\">GEN 46:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:25\">NUM 35:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:21\">2CH 36:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:11\">ISA 51:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:4-Isa61:6\">ISA 61:4–61:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:17\">ISA 63:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:14-Jer16:15\">JER 16:14–16:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:10-Jer29:14\">JER 29:10–29:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:3\">JER 30:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:37\">JER 32:37</a></p>",
